1. Introduction
Welcome to SafeHer! These Terms and Conditions ("Terms") govern your access and use of the SafeHer mobile application ("App"). By downloading, installing, or using SafeHer, you agree to comply with these Terms. If you do not agree, you must discontinue use immediately.
2. Eligibility
•	You must be at least 18 years old to use SafeHer. If you are under 18, you may only use the App with the consent of a parent or guardian.
•	You must have a Google account to register and use the App.
•	SafeHer is designed to assist individuals in safety situations, including women, children, elderly individuals, and anyone seeking personal security solutions.
3. Permitted Use
•	SafeHer must only be used for personal safety purposes and not for any unlawful activity.
•	Users must not trigger false alarms or misuse emergency features.
•	The App provides real-time location tracking, emergency alerts, and video/audio recording for emergency contacts and law enforcement in case of threats.
4. Permissions and Data Usage
SafeHer requires the following permissions to function correctly:
•	Location Access : Enables real-time tracking for safety navigation and threat detection.
•	Internet and Network State: Facilitates connectivity for emergency alerts and online services.
•	Camera and Microphone: Captures video and audio evidence during emergencies.
•	SMS and Notifications: Sends emergency alerts to designated contacts.
•	Storage Access: Stores recorded media securely.
•	Vibration and Phone State: Ensures functional feedback and call handling.
•	Battery Optimization: Ensures uninterrupted background operation of critical safety features.
5. Privacy and Security
•	SafeHer collects personal details such as name, phone number, and email for account registration and identification.
•	Emergency contact information is only accessed but not stored.
•	Location tracking is active only when safety features are enabled and stops when deactivated.
•	SafeHer does not share user data with third parties.
•	User data is encrypted and stored securely, complying with GDPR and India's IT Act.
6. Subscription and Monetization
•	SafeHer operates on a freemium model, offering premium safety features via in-app purchases and subscription plans.
•	The App does not use advertisements.
7. Third-Party Services
•	SafeHer integrates Firebase for backend services, Google Maps for location tracking, and a payment gateway for transactions.
•	Third-party services are governed by their respective terms and policies.
8. Limitation of Liability
•	SafeHer is provided "as is" without any warranties.
•	While the App enhances personal safety, it does not guarantee absolute security.
•	Users assume full responsibility for their reliance on the App.
9. Termination
•	Violation of these Terms may result in immediate suspension or termination of access to SafeHer.
•	SafeHer reserves the right to modify, discontinue, or update the App at any time.
